<section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl space-y-8">
  <header class="space-y-2">
    <h1 class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
      <i aria-hidden="true" class="fa-solid fa-paper-plane text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100"></i>
      <span>Submit an organization</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">Help grow our community! If you know a Calgary-based community group that should be in the directory (or want to update an existing listing), we'd love to hear from you.</p>
    <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300">Need help understanding the types and interests? See our <a href="/info/" class="text-brand-orange hover:underline dark:text-cyan-400">Types & Interests guide</a>.</p>
  </header>

  <div class="prose max-w-none">
    <h2>Guidelines</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Keep it factual</strong>: a short description + contact info is best.</li>
      <li><strong>Include a primary link</strong>: website is ideal; otherwise a social profile.</li>
      <li><strong>Pick one type</strong>: choose the closest match.</li>
      <li><strong>Pick 1–3 interests</strong>: use the existing interest tags where possible.</li>
      <li><strong>Don’t share private info</strong>: only public contact details.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Types</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><code>Nonprofit</code> - Registered organizations (societies, charities)</li>
      <li><code>Grassroots</code> - Activist or advocacy-focused groups</li>
      <li><code>Club</code> - Social or interest-based groups</li>
      <li><code>Chapter</code> - Local branch of a larger organization</li>
      <li><code>Cooperative</code> - Collective run by multiple organizations</li>
      <li><code>Small Business</code> - For-profit businesses serving community needs</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Interests</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><code>anti-racism</code></li>
      <li><code>arts</code></li>
      <li><code>book</code> - Book Clubs</li>
      <li><code>culture and heritage</code></li>
      <li><code>disability/neurodivergent</code></li>
      <li><code>education</code></li>
      <li><code>environment</code></li>
      <li><code>general</code></li>
      <li><code>health-wellness</code></li>
      <li><code>indigenous</code></li>
      <li><code>international-solidarity</code></li>
      <li><code>justice</code></li>
